President Biden has declared a major disaster in California due to the Caldor Fire and has ordered federal assistance to support recovery efforts. This assistance includes funding for emergency work, repairing or replacing damaged facilities, and implementing hazard mitigation measures. Andrew Grant has been named as the Federal Coordinating Officer for the recovery operations in the affected areas. Further designations may be made in the future based on damage assessments. For more information, media can contact the FEMA News Desk.